 the ideas of geography, or 'world- writing', to reshape the symbolic import of the female body and territory to create new identities. The book demonstrates how early modern mapmakers and dramatists ? men and women ? conceived of and constructed identities within a discourse of fluid ideas about space and gender.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 03. Jan 2023) 0aCartography in literaturexHistoryyEarly modern, 1500-1700. 0aTheaterxHistoryyEarly modern, 1500-1700zEngland. 0aWomen in literaturexHistoryyEarly modern, 1500-1700. 4aEarly Modern Studies. 4aGender and Sexuality Studies. 4aHistory, Art History, and Archaeology. 4aLiterary Theory, Criticism, and History. 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / Drama.2bisacsh  aGeography, Renaissance drama, women, representation.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertAmsterdam University Press Complete eBook-Package 2019z978311066152108iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2019 Englishz978311061076508iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2019z9783110664232oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Literary, Cultural and Area Stud. 2019 Englishz978311061036908iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Literary, Cultural and Area Studies 2019z9783110606348oZDB-23-DKU40uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9789048544226?locatt=mode:legacy40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9789048544226423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9789048544226/original  a978-3-11-061036-9  EBOOK PACKAGE Literary, Cultural and Area Stud. 2019 Englishb2019  a978-3-11-061076-5  EBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2019 Englishb2019  a978-3-11-066152-1  Amsterdam University Press Complete eBook-Package 2019b2019  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_HICS  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_E